And now a page from our "Sunday Morning" almanac: September 30, 1882, 136 years ago today, and OUR COUNTING FURTHER... the day the future physicist Johannes Wilhelm "Hans" Geiger was born in Germany.
Geiger developed a method to detect and measure radioactivity, an invention that eventually led to the device called the Geiger counter.
