Mickelson out of the race and out of Saturday's Ryder Cup
American Phil Mickelson will set a record when he plays his 47th Ryder Cup match on Sunday, but he will have to get in shape to prevent it from becoming an unfortunate milestone.
Mickelson, playing for a record 12th time in the biennial event, was ejected by captain Jim Furyk for Saturday's four-ball and four-number games.
